Here's a PlantUML component diagram focusing on performance and deployment for the Scantron system:

```plantuml
@startuml rackerlabs_scantron

!define RECTANGLE class

skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor<<performance>> LightGreen
  BorderColor<<performance>> Green
}

cloud "External Systems" {
  [Big Data Analytics Platform]
}

node "Console Server" {
  [Nginx] <<performance>> 
  [Django Web Application] <<performance>>
  [Redis Queue] <<performance>>
  database "PostgreSQL"
  [NFS Client]
}

node "Engine Node" {
  [Scanning Engine] <<performance>>
  [nmap/masscan] <<performance>>
  [NFS Client]
}

node "Shared Storage" {
  [NFS Server] <<performance>>
}

[Nginx] --> [Django Web Application] : "Proxy/SSL Termination"
[Django Web Application] --> [Redis Queue] : "Async Tasks"
[Django Web Application] --> PostgreSQL : "Data Storage"
[Django Web Application] --> [NFS Client] : "File Access"
[Scanning Engine] --> [nmap/masscan] : "Executes"
[Scanning Engine] --> [NFS Client] : "Results Storage"
[NFS Client] --> [NFS Server] : "File Share"
[Django Web Application] <--> [Scanning Engine] : "REST API"
[Django Web Application] --> [Big Data Analytics Platform] : "CSV Export"

@enduml
```

This diagram highlights the following performance and deployment aspects:

1. Nginx as a performance-enhancing proxy and SSL terminator.
2. Redis Queue for asynchronous task processing, improving responsiveness.
3. Distributed scanning engines for parallel execution and scalability.
4. NFS for shared storage, allowing efficient file sharing between components.
5. High-performance scanning tools (nmap/masscan) on engine nodes.
6. Separation of the console and engine components for distributed deployment.
7. Integration with external big data analytics platform for scalable data processing.

The components marked with <<performance>> are particularly important for system performance and scalability.